{"questionId":"22445318","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One of the goats, Brenda, fights with the other goats. The farmer plans to place a second fence with a fixed length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> metres between the wall and the hedge to form a small triangular field inside <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> for Brenda.</p>\n<p>The information is shown on the following diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/70de0d2dff356e6ec50e1b47ba9362f15f9bbe20.png\" width=\"671\" height=\"269\"></p>\n<p>The small triangular field <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OCD</mi></math> has an area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> be the distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OC</mi></math> and let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> be the distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OD</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, determine the two possible lengths of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OC</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to eliminate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>120</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>240</mn><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the intersection of the graph of their cosine rule equation and the graph of their area formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> only if their graphs are of functions with the same subject e.g. both \"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>…</mo></math>\" or both \"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>…</mo></math>\".</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1300</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4673</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22445318","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.9c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, determine the two possible lengths of OC.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
